{"id": 243311170, "title": "The fairytale town 90 minutes away from Birmingham that is as enchanting as it looks", "text": "For those looking for a tranquil escape, Cirencester in Gloucestershire is the perfect weekend retreat. Nestled between Cheltenham and Swindon, this charming town isn't exactly a bargain when it comes to property prices, with the average home costing around \u00a3395K, as per Rightmove data. Often dubbed as the 'capital of the Cotswolds', Cirencester holds a significant title and also has a twin-town relationship with Itzehoe in Germany, a bond that was celebrated back in 1982. Things to do Rodmarton Manor, a privately-owned residence, invites visitors to wander through its stunning eight-acre garden filled with beautiful flowers, trees, and lawns, reports MyLondon. Another must-see is The Parish Church of St John Baptist, a historical site that has been in use for over a thousand years. The main section of the church dates back over 500 years, and it hosts daily Eucharist and Evening Prayer, along with mid-day prayers. For thrill-seekers, the town offers exciting 4X4 Off-Road driving experiences. Here, drivers of all abilities, guided by an experienced instructor, can learn how to tackle vertical climbs, vertical descents, water troughs and axle twisters. And naturally, after all that excitement, you're bound to be hungry. That's where Amore Mio comes in. Boasting a five-star rating on TripAdvisor, this Italian restaurant serves up delicious pizza, pasta, and risotto. One happy diner even penned: \"Great restaurant, beautiful food, attentive, friendly staff. Fresh bread and pizza made in front of you in a pizza oven. \"Delicious, original desserts. Definitely recommend one of the nicest Italian restaurants we've been to'\"", "summary": "From historic landmarks to thrilling activities, here's a round-up of everything you can see and do in Cirencester, the 'capital of the Cotswolds'", "url": "https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/travel/fairytale-town-90-minutes-away-29425435", "image": "https://i2-prod.birminghammail.co.uk/news/uk-news/article29425423.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/1_gettyimages-1445791659.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 04:30:00", "author": "Jamie Brassington,Rafi Mauro-Benady", "authors": ["Jamie Brassington", "Rafi Mauro-Benady"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.818}